libari - a light fontain library
================================
See http://itk.samfundet.no/dok/ari for more/updated information.

Library 
-------
The library contains multiple modules and the package libari.demos. Documentation of all methods is available through starting a Python shell, loading the module and running help(libari.modulename).

Configuration
libari.config has no methods, but contains some useful variables and a data struct which describes the physical layout of the wall.

Canvas
All canvas modules implements the base class libari.canvas. Available modules
includes:
- libari.wall paints on the physical wall via the helper libari.wallnet. This
  module is normally used.
- libari.martha is a simulator and paints i a GUI window on your machine
  instead of the wall. This is usefull for development of new plugins.

Demos
The package libari.demos.* contains the demo effects for the wall.


Installation from RCS
---------------------
The following procedure installs the latest version of libari into
/usr/lib/python2.4/site-packages/libari/:

bzr branch http://itk.samfundet.no/bzr/jodal/ari/ ari.my-branch/
cd ari.my-branch/libari/
python setup.py install


API documentation
-----------------
Use Python's built in help() function on the modules for documentation.


Usage example
-------------
Turn all diodes on, then off:

$ python
>>> import libari.wall
>>> w = libari.wall.Wall()
>>> w.blank(99)
>>> w.blank(0)
>>> 

Use of the Martha simulator is analogous:

$ python
>>> import libari.martha
>>> m = libari.martha.Martha()
>>> m.blank(99)
>>> m.blank(0)
>>> 

